<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-08T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-08T03:00:00-05:00" n="79" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/4332: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Addis
                                            Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-08T11:00:00+03:00">May 8, 1936—11
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 7:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>315. Ethiopian authorities have departed from Harrar and as Italians
                                have not yet arrived there, a situation has arisen similar to that
                                just experienced in Addis Ababa. British Consul at Harrar with guard
                                of 20 Somalis is endeavoring protect foreign nationals or evacuate
                                them to Diré Dawa. No Americans at or near Harrar.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>